<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="440" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1049,1362]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440">
<collectingCountry box="[151,182,1050,1074]" name="American Samoa" pageId="3" pageNumber="440">As</collectingCountry>
explained by 
<bibRefCitation box="[344,584,1049,1074]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" refString="Moreira, F. F. F., Nessimian, J. L., Rudio, J. A. &amp; Salles, F. F. (2010) New species and new records of Veliidae from Espirito Santo State and adjacent Minas Gerais State, Brazil, with notes on nomenclature (Insecta: Heteroptera: Gerromorpha). Journal of Natural History, 44, 2761 - 2801. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222933.2010.512423" type="journal article">
Moreira 
<emphasis box="[443,500,1049,1073]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="440">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[516,575,1050,1074]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Nemesio" box="[641,924,1049,1074]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" refString="Nemesio, A. &amp; Melo, A. L. (2012) Nomenclatural issues in Rhagovelia Mayr (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerromorpha: Veliidae). Zootaxa, 3230, 65 - 66." type="journal article" year="2012">
Nemésio &amp; Melo (
<number box="[855,916,1050,1074]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" value="2012.0">2012</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, new species mentioned on the identification key to the 
<taxonomicName box="[272,400,1085,1109]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Rhagovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[272,400,1085,1109]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="440">Rhagovelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of Minas Gerais provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser" box="[743,996,1085,1110]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" refString="Nieser, N. &amp; Melo, A. L. (1997) Os Heteropteros Aquaticos de Minas Gerais Guia Introdutorio com Chave de Identificacao para as Especies de Nepomorpha e Gerromorpha. Editora UFMG, Belo Horizonte, 177 pp." type="book" year="1997">
Nieser &amp; Melo (
<number box="[930,988,1086,1110]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" value="1997.0">1997</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
must be considered valid according to the rules of zoological nomenclature at that period. Four of the species described on the key have been addressed by 
<bibRefCitation box="[185,419,1157,1182]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" refString="Moreira, F. F. F., Nessimian, J. L., Rudio, J. A. &amp; Salles, F. F. (2010) New species and new records of Veliidae from Espirito Santo State and adjacent Minas Gerais State, Brazil, with notes on nomenclature (Insecta: Heteroptera: Gerromorpha). Journal of Natural History, 44, 2761 - 2801. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222933.2010.512423" type="journal article">
Moreira 
<emphasis box="[282,338,1157,1181]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="440">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[352,411,1158,1182]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Nemesio" box="[472,749,1157,1182]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" refString="Nemesio, A. &amp; Melo, A. L. (2012) Nomenclatural issues in Rhagovelia Mayr (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerromorpha: Veliidae). Zootaxa, 3230, 65 - 66." type="journal article" year="2012">
Nemésio &amp; Melo (
<number box="[680,741,1158,1182]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" value="2012.0">2012</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, but there was actually a fifth description on the key. On page 
<number box="[151,193,1194,1218]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" value="109.0">109</number>
of 
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser" box="[239,504,1193,1218]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" refString="Nieser, N. &amp; Melo, A. L. (1997) Os Heteropteros Aquaticos de Minas Gerais Guia Introdutorio com Chave de Identificacao para as Especies de Nepomorpha e Gerromorpha. Editora UFMG, Belo Horizonte, 177 pp." type="book" year="1997">
Nieser &amp; Melo (
<number box="[436,496,1194,1218]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" value="1997.0">1997</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, step 
<number box="[577,605,1193,1218]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" value="39.0">39</number>
b of the key, there is the mention to a new species named 
<taxonomicName authority="Nieser &amp; Melo, 1997" authorityName="Nieser &amp; Melo" authorityYear="1997" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Rhagovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachymeri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="440">Rhagovelia pachymeri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser" box="[280,535,1229,1254]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" refString="Nieser, N. &amp; Melo, A. L. (1997) Os Heteropteros Aquaticos de Minas Gerais Guia Introdutorio com Chave de Identificacao para as Especies de Nepomorpha e Gerromorpha. Editora UFMG, Belo Horizonte, 177 pp." type="book" year="1997">
Nieser &amp; Melo, 
<number box="[476,535,1230,1254]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which unlike the other four was not described again at 
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" refString="Nieser, N. &amp; Polhemus, D. A. (1999) Four new species of Rhagovelia (Heteroptera: Veliidae) from Minas Gerais (Brazil), with a key to the regional species of the angustipes complex. Aquatic Insects, 21, 53 - 76. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1076 / aqin. 21.1.53.4540" type="journal article" year="1999">
Nieser &amp; Polhemus (
<number box="[159,220,1266,1290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. During a visit to 
<collectionCode box="[429,502,1266,1290]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/9yp6-zxp9" name="Sao Paulo, Museu de Zoologia da Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="3" pageNumber="440">MZSP</collectionCode>
by 
<collectionCode box="[544,618,1266,1289]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440">FFFM</collectionCode>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[671,719,1266,1290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName box="[855,1004,1265,1289]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Rhagovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachymeri">
<emphasis box="[855,1004,1265,1289]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="440">R. pachymeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been examined and revealed to be conspecific with 
<taxonomicName box="[346,463,1301,1325]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Rhagovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis box="[346,463,1301,1325]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="440">R. robusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, we herein propose the synonymy between the two species. This fact was probably what leaded the species to be excluded from the paper by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser" box="[905,1209,1337,1362]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" refString="Nieser, N. &amp; Polhemus, D. A. (1999) Four new species of Rhagovelia (Heteroptera: Veliidae) from Minas Gerais (Brazil), with a key to the regional species of the angustipes complex. Aquatic Insects, 21, 53 - 76. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1076 / aqin. 21.1.53.4540" type="journal article" year="1999">
Nieser &amp; Polhemus (
<number box="[1140,1201,1338,1362]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
